Arduino Uno Code:
```
// Potentiometer voltage divider
// This code interfaces with a circuit that has a potentiometer configured as a voltage divider.
// When the input voltage is greater than or equal to 2.5V, it turns on an I/O pin (D2), otherwise it turns off the I/O pin.

// Potentiometer on Analog Input 0
#define PIN_POT A0
// LED on Digital I/O 2
#define PIN_LED 2

// Threshold voltage (2.5V)
#define THRESHOLD_VOLTAGE 2.5

// the setup function runs once when you press reset or power the board
void setup() {
    // Initialize LED pin to output mode
    pinMode(PIN_LED, OUTPUT);
}

// the loop function runs over and over again forever
void loop() {
    // Read the potentiometer value
    int potValue = analogRead(PIN_POT);

    // Convert the potentiometer value to voltage
    float voltage = (float)potValue * (5.0 / 1023.0);

    // Check if the voltage is greater than or equal to the threshold voltage
    if (voltage >= THRESHOLD_VOLTAGE) {
        digitalWrite(PIN_LED, HIGH); // Turn LED ON
    } else {
        digitalWrite(PIN_LED, LOW);  // Turn LED OFF
    }

    delay(100); // Short delay for stability
}
```

Instructions:
```
- This code uses only standard libraries. No additional libraries are required in the library manager.
- Assemble circuit and program as normal.
```
